      "content": "It's understandable to want to avoid the ER, but considering your ankle is severely swollen and you have difficulty walking on it, it's best to err on the side of caution. RICE (rest, ice, compression, and elevation) can help alleviate symptoms, but a more serious injury, such as a sprain or fracture, may require medical attention. If you can't bear weight or feel severe pain, consider going to the ER or urgent care instead of self-managing for a few days.",
